uk = pd.read_csv('/content/drive/MyDrive/Citadel Datathon 2021/Finance/^FTSE.csv')
ukgdp = pd.read_csv('/content/drive/MyDrive/Citadel Datathon 2021/Finance/ukgdp.csv')
ukgdp=ukgdp[['Unnamed: 0','Monthly GDP','Agriculture','Production','Construction','Services']]
ukgdp = ukgdp.dropna()
ukgdp = ukgdp.loc[[277,278,279,280,281,282,283,284,285,286,287,288],:]
ukgdp=ukgdp.reset_index()
ukgdp['Monthly GDP']=ukgdp['Monthly GDP'].astype('float')
ukgdp['Agriculture']=ukgdp['Agriculture'].astype('float')
ukgdp['Production']=ukgdp['Production'].astype('float')
ukgdp['Construction']=ukgdp['Construction'].astype('float')
ukgdp['Services']=ukgdp['Services'].astype('float')
ukgdp['total']=ukgdp['Agriculture']+ukgdp['Production']+ukgdp['Construction']+ukgdp['Services']+ukgdp['Monthly GDP']

for x in range(0,12):
  ukgdp['Unnamed: 0'][x]='15-'+str(x+1)+'-2020'
ukgdp['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(ukgdp['Unnamed: 0'])
ukgdp=ukgdp[['Date','Monthly GDP','Agriculture','Production','Construction','Services','total']]

uk = uk[['Date','Adj Close']]
uk['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(uk['Date'])
uk = uk.rename({'Date':'date'}, axis='columns')

temp = owid.loc[owid['location']=='United Kingdom']
temp=temp.drop(columns=['iso_code','location'])

uk = uk.merge(temp,on='date')
uk = uk.dropna()

ukgdp['total']=ukgdp['total']/ukgdp['total'].max()
uk['Adj Close']=uk['Adj Close']/uk['Adj Close'].max()
uk['reproduction_rate']=uk['reproduction_rate']/uk['reproduction_rate'].max()

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(uk['date'],uk['Adj Close'])
ax.set_ylabel('Adj Close',color='blue')
ax.set_xlabel('Date')

ax2 = ax.twinx()
# ax2.set_ylabel('Stringency Index',color='red')
ax2.plot(uk['date'],uk['reproduction_rate'], color='red')
plt.title('UK Stock Index vs Reproduction Rate')

ax.plot(ukgdp['Date'],ukgdp['total'], color='black')
ax.set_ylabel('GDP')
ax.set_xlabel('Date')


cor1 = uk['Adj Close'][0:100].corr(uk['reproduction_rate'][0:100],method='spearman')
cor2 = uk['Adj Close'][100:-1].corr(uk['reproduction_rate'][100:-1],method='spearman')
cor3 = uk['Adj Close'][0:50].corr(uk['reproduction_rate'][0:50])
